00:07:32.900 --> 00:07:35.130
But essentially, what
a design change log is,

00:07:35.130 --> 00:07:38.720
it's actually really simple.

00:07:38.720 --> 00:07:41.360
It's a table, three columns.

00:07:41.360 --> 00:07:42.720
You've got a date.

00:07:42.720 --> 00:07:44.740
You've got some action
you made on your design

00:07:44.740 --> 00:07:46.448
to change it in some
way, and then you've

00:07:46.448 --> 00:07:48.137
got the reason why
you made the change.

00:07:48.137 --> 00:07:49.970
And every time you make
a significant change

00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:55.620
to your project, and/or every
day you work on your project,

00:07:55.620 --> 00:07:59.474
you make another entry so
that your team and the people

00:07:59.474 --> 00:08:01.640
working on it and the people
looking at your project

00:08:01.640 --> 00:08:05.040
to see where it is now can see
why you made the decisions you

00:08:05.040 --> 00:08:07.970
made and what
decisions you made,

00:08:07.970 --> 00:08:10.320
what features you dropped,
what features you added,

00:08:10.320 --> 00:08:11.950
what problems you
were trying to solve

00:08:11.950 --> 00:08:14.650
when you made those changes.

